{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Cookie Dough","content":["Preheat oven to 350°F. Line baking sheets with parchment and set aside.","Place chocolate into mixing bowl and grind <nobr>10 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>.","Add butter and melt <nobr>3 min\/160°F\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add sugar, eggs, vanilla and salt and mix <nobr>5 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Add flour and mix <nobr>5 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and mix a further <nobr>5 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Scoop 2 tablespoons of dough for each cookie and place onto prepared baking sheets (approx. 2 in. apart). Flatten cookie dough (approx. ¼ in. thick) with the palm of your hand or bottom of a glass. Bake one sheet after another for 12-15 minutes (350°F), until the edges and middle are set. Cool on baking sheet (approx. 5 min.) then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely before frosting. Clean mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Frosting","content":["Place confectioners sugar, milk and peppermint extract into mixing bowl and mix <nobr>20 sec\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and mix a further <nobr>20 sec\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Transfer frosting into a bowl and set aside.","Spread frosting onto tops of cooled cookies and sprinkle with candy pieces. Let frosting set completely before packaging or serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Cookie Dough","content":["4 ½ oz semi-sweet chocolate chips","4 ½ oz unsalted butter, cut into pieces, room temperature","4 oz sugar","2 large eggs","1 tsp vanilla extract","&frac18; tsp salt","12 oz all-purpose flour"]},{"title":"Frosting","content":["12 oz confectioners sugar","2 oz whole milk","1 tsp peppermint extract","candy canes or peppermint candies, broken into pieces, to garnish"]}],"id":"r263125","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-T4PG3QQr4nQ\/XZWdQT__FoI\/AAAAAAAAejk\/nMc1I0of1mosmsIxFmVPJ2NiAw_TvR3twCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_DuWYywInfcEZMZQE.png","title":"Peppermint Frosted Chocolate Cookies","publishedAt":"2017